# Route Resolution Spec

## Overview

This document replaces the previous `landing_page_spec` and clarifies the frontend/backend page and route resolution flow in Skaia. It covers both the homepage (landing page) and generic page selection, including real-time updates and cache strategies.

---

## Cold Load: User Visits `/`

```
Browser => GET /
  └── nginx serves index.html (SSR-injected <title>, OG, favicon)
        └── React mounts <Index /> => <PageBuilder /> (no slug prop)

PageBuilder mounts:
  └── usePageData(editingCount > 0).refresh() called with no slug

refresh() — index mode (no slug):
  1. GET /config/pages/landing-slug  =>  { "slug": "my-page" }
  2. GET /config/pages/my-page       =>  full PageBuilderPage object

Why two requests:
  /config/pages/index is a SINGLE CDN cache key — when the landing page is
  swapped, Cloudflare serves the old page from cache.
  /config/pages/{slug} has a UNIQUE cache key per page — always fresh.

  The landing-slug endpoint is tiny JSON (< 50 bytes), never worth caching.
  The per-slug fetch gets the actual content from a cache key that matches
  the page it returns.
```

## Hot Update: Landing Page Swapped (WS Connected)

```
Admin selects new landing page in PageBuilder toolbar:

Frontend:
  1. Cancel any queued BBR save timer (prevent stale sections write-back)
  2. Clear pendingSectionsRef
  3. PUT /config/pages/landing-page  { slug: "new-page" }
  4. Clear sections + sectionsSourced
  5. Call refresh() => two-step fetch (landing-slug => page by slug)

Backend (setLandingPage handler):
  1. Upsert "landing_page_slug" in site_config
  2. Fetch full new page (enriched with owner/editors)
  3. Dispatch two WS broadcasts:
     a. page:update   { action: "landing_page_changed", data: <full page> }
     b. config:update  { action: "landing_page_updated", data: { slug } }

All other clients receive (via useWebSocketSync):

  page:update => window "page:live:event":
    usePageData handler sees action === "landing_page_changed"
    If in index mode (no requestedSlugRef.current):
      => setPage(data) directly — ZERO HTTP requests, completely cache-proof

  config:update => window "config:live:event":
    PageBuilder handler sees action === "landing_page_updated"
    If !slug && editingCount === 0:
      => refresh() — two-step fetch as fallback
    CustomPages handler re-fetches browse => badge updates correctly
```

## Page Content Updated (Same Landing Page)

```
Editor saves a section on the landing page:

Frontend:
  BBR adaptive save pipeline => PUT /config/pages/{id}
  HTTP response = updated page (authoritative for sender)

Backend:
  BroadcastPageExceptUser(userID, "page_updated", enrichedPage)
  => page:update sent to all clients EXCEPT the one who saved

Other clients:
  page:live:event with action === "page_updated"
  If data.slug matches currentSlugRef OR data.id matches page.id:
    If editing => hold in pendingDataRef, set pendingIncoming flag
    If not editing => applyIncomingData(data) directly (no HTTP)
```

## Key Endpoints

| Method | Path                       | Auth     | Purpose                      |
| ------ | -------------------------- | -------- | ---------------------------- |
| GET    | /config/pages/landing-slug | none     | Resolve current landing slug |
| GET    | /config/pages/index        | opt JWT  | Fetch landing page (legacy)  |
| GET    | /config/pages/{slug}       | opt JWT  | Fetch page by slug           |
| PUT    | /config/pages/landing-page | JWT+perm | Set landing page slug        |
| PUT    | /config/pages/{id}         | JWT+perm | Update page content          |

## WS Events

| Channel       | Action               | Payload          | Triggered By   |
| ------------- | -------------------- | ---------------- | -------------- |
| page:update   | landing_page_changed | full Page object | setLandingPage |
| config:update | landing_page_updated | { slug }         | setLandingPage |
| page:update   | page_updated         | full Page object | updatePage     |
| page:update   | page_deleted         | { id }           | deletePage     |

## Invariants

- **No `is_index` column.** Landing page is determined solely by `landing_page_slug` in `site_config`.
- **Frontend NEVER calls `/config/pages/index` for the landing page.** It uses the two-step flow: landing-slug => fetch by slug. The index endpoint exists for backwards compatibility only.
- **WS push is the primary update path.** HTTP is the fallback. `landing_page_changed` carries the full page object so clients can swap without any HTTP request.
- **Save pipeline cancellation on swap.** When the landing page is changed, `saveTimerRef` is cleared and `pendingSectionsRef` is nulled to prevent stale sections from the old page being written to the new one.
- **applyIncomingData preserves per-user fields.** `is_liked` and `can_delete` are not in the broadcast — the setter merges incoming data while keeping the local user's computed fields intact.

## Anti-Patterns (Things That Broke Before)

1. **Single cache key for index endpoint.** `/config/pages/index` returns different pages depending on config, but CDNs cache by URL. Swapping the landing page serves stale content. Fix: two-step slug resolution.
2. **307 redirect from getIndex to getBySlug.** `fetch()` follows the redirect transparently, but the redirected response confused PageBuilder's page creation logic (null page => ensurePage => creates "landing" page). Fix: serve inline from getIndex, but frontend uses landing-slug endpoint.
3. **Broadcasting only the slug on config:update.** The frontend needs the full page data to render sections. Sending just `{slug}` forced an HTTP refetch that hit the stale CDN cache. Fix: broadcast full page via page:update.
4. **Not cancelling save timer on swap.** The old page's queued save would fire after the new page loaded, overwriting the new page's content with old sections. Fix: clear timer + pendingSectionsRef before the swap.
